Spotlight Card Analysis

(Cards with a different background color are in the top 20 for adoption count for that character.)

Star Players

Cards expected to be highly effective. This includes cards that demonstrate their true value in critical late-game situations.

  • Daiyousei, Lively Assistant
  • Frozen Specimen
  • Gift of Nature
  • Icicle Dance
  • Water Blanket
  • Wingbeats Flight
  • Wolf Fur

Honor Students

Cards with exceptionally high tendency scores in both attack and defense or with silver(gold) medals, expected to perform consistently well in all situations.

  • Autumnal Harvest
  • Blizzard
  • Cool Entrance
  • Cool Party
  • Exteeending Aaaarm
  • Frozen Throne
  • Instant Freeze
  • Moonlit Lotus
  • News Fabrication
  • On Thin Ice
  • Rainbow Danmaku Dupion
  • Refreshing Breeze
  • Stunning Summer Ice
  • The Reclusive Sage

Balancers

Well-rounded cards that improve deck stability by balancing offense and defense.

  • Waves of Reversed Scale

High-Return Attackers

Cards with high-return potential, accepting a manageable defensive risk.

  • Call on Friends
  • Clean Energy
  • Fairy's Wake Up
  • Ice Barrier
  • Kasumi, Mansion Maid
  • Sakura-Colored Sea

Stability-Focused Defenders

Cards that excel at stabilizing combat, accepting a manageable offensive risk.

  • Absolute Zero
  • Diamond Breath
  • Ever Cool Seasonal Fantasia
  • Fairy Assembly
  • Fairy On Ice
  • Frozen Orb
  • Letty, Winter Embodied
  • Princess Undine

Counter Cards

Cards with low overall stats that have proven to be decisive (medal-winning) in specific, high-impact situations.

  • Ice-Forged Blade

Card Classification Criteria

Each card is evaluated based on the following conditions in order from top to bottom, and is classified into the first type it matches.

Star Players

  • Overall Performance Score < 100 BUT has a notable performance against the Act 4 Boss.
  • Has a medal AND all notable performances are concentrated in the late game (Act 3 or 4).
  • Attack Tendency > 1.0 OR Defense Tendency > 1.0.

Honor Students

  • Has a Gold Medal ü•á or Silver Medal ü•à (Highest Priority).
  • (Attack Tendency > 0.25 AND Defense Tendency > 0.25) AND has at least one Big Star ‚≠ê (tendency > 0.75).
  • Has a Bronze Medal ü•â or better AND (Attack Tendency > 0.25 AND Defense Tendency > 0.25) AND has at least one Star ‚òÜ (tendency > 0.5).
  • Otherwise, meets ( (Tendency Sum >= 0.75 AND has a medal) OR (Tendency Sum >= 1.0) ) AND (Overall Performance Score >= 100).

Balancers

  • Among cards not classified into any other type, those with both positive Attack and Defense Tendencies, and a sum of these tendencies >= 0.5.

High-Return Attackers

  • Attack Tendency >= 0.25 AND Defense Tendency is within the range of -0.75 to +0.25.

Stability-Focused Defenders

  • Defense Tendency >= 0.25 AND Attack Tendency is within the range of -0.75 to +0.25.

Counter Cards

  • Tendency Sum < -1.5 AND has a medal.
